<title>FRANCE: Austria's Klima sees danger if euro delayed.</title>
<headline>Austria's Klima sees danger if euro delayed.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Austrian Chancellor Viktor Klima has warned of &quot;serious danger&quot; if the timetable for a planned single European currency slips and urged a redoubled effort to cut budget deficits and help jobs.</p>
<p>&quot;I think the moment has come to send a strong signal to the people of Europe to convince them that the single currency will not be put off,&quot; he said in an interview to appear in the conservative French daily Le Figaro on Friday. &quot;Any delay would represent a serious danger.&quot;</p>
</text>
